A vintage-style illustration of a bustling Bavarian beer hall scene, but instead of beer steins, a frustrated waitress in traditional dirndl carries a massive ornate serving tray overflowing with tiny glowing data packets and miniature smartphone icons. The patrons at long wooden tables are silhouettes of mobile devices - phones and tablets - waiting impatiently with empty tables before them. Golden warm lighting from hanging lanterns creates pools of light and shadow. The waitress is caught mid-stride between the kitchen door (emanating a cool blue server-room glow) and the distant tables, her path marked by dotted lines showing her many trips back and forth. The scene has a 1920s travel poster aesthetic with muted ochres, deep browns, and pops of electric blue, printed on slightly aged cream paper with visible grain texture.
